{"questionId":"9085608","questionHtml":"<p>A standing wave with a first harmonic of frequency <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> is formed on a string fixed at both ends.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/41e94b5e4de150d66d890c5a4082ff83bea1074f.png\"></p>\n<p>The frequency of the third harmonic is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>What is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mfrac></math>?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; 3</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9085608","referenceCode":"23M.1A.SL.TZ1.17","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A standing wave with a first harmonic of frequency f1 is formed on a string fixed at both ends. The frequency of the third harmonic is f3. What is f1f3? A. 3 B. 32 C. 23 D. 13","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"17","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["C. Wave behaviour","C.4 Standing waves and resonance"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}